Certainly! You can write a simple JavaScript function to print 'hello world' to the console by using the `console.log()` method. Here's how you can do it:

```javascript
function printHelloWorld() {
    console.log('hello world');
}

// Call the function to print 'hello world'
printHelloWorld();
```

This code defines a function named `printHelloWorld` that, when called, will output 'hello world' to the console. You can run this code in any JavaScript environment, such as a web browser's developer console or a Node.js environment, to see the output.
